This package contains two plugins:
- plg_jresearch_databases_modified_publication_form
It modifies the form for adding/editing publications and adds a button next to citekey field which allows
to retrieve publications of type article from external databases like PubMED using the publication ID in the remote
database. 

- plg_jresearch_xmlrpc_retrieve_records_external_databases
It provides a XML-RPC interface for retrieving information about publications of type article. The result is
serialized using XML-RPC responses syntax. The following snippet shows a remote invokation using PHP.


Remote method: getRemotePublication(string publicationId)

<?php
/**
* Returns the information about a publication located in an external database
* @param string $p1
* @param int $debug when 1 (or 2) will enable debugging of the underlying xmlrpc call (defaults to 0)
* @return array (or an xmlrpcresp obj instance if call fails)
*/
function xmlrpc_jresearch_getRemotePublication ($p1, $debug=0) {
$client =& new xmlrpc_client(JOOMLA_URL.'/xmlrpc/', 'localhost', 80);
$client->return_type = 'xmlrpcvals';
$client->setDebug($debug);
$msg =& new xmlrpcmsg('jresearch.getRemotePublication');
$p1 =& new xmlrpcval($p1, 'string');
$msg->addparam($p1);
$res =& $client->send($msg, 0, '');
if ($res->faultcode()) return $res; else return php_xmlrpc_decode($res->value());
}
?> 

This is equivalent to do a HTTP request using POST method to JOOMLA_URL.'/xmlrpc/index.php'. The body of the request looks like:
<methodCall><methodName>jresearch.getRemotePublication</methodName><params><param><value><string>[PUBLICATION_ID]</string></value></param></params></methodCall>

Further parameters are supported in URL:
service: Name of the service used the publication will be retrieved from. This release only supports PubMED.
format: xml(default), json. In both cases, result will be serialized using XML-RPC responses syntax. 'xml' will use XML-RPC struct data type whereas 'json' will use string data type whose value is the publication encoded using JSON data format.
short: 0 (default) , 1. If 0, ALL the information stored in external database about the publication will be delivered, otherwise only fields concerning J!Research publications definition will be retrieved. This parameter only works when format=json.

XML-RPC response sample with format=xml:
<?xml version="1.0"?>
<methodResponse>
<params>
<param>
<value><struct>
<member><name>citekey</name>
<value><string>173406</string></value>
</member>
<member><name>title</name>
<value><string>[Letter: EPR study of bacteriorhodopsin-containing systems]</string></value>
</member>
<member><name>abstract</name>
<value><string></string></value>
</member>
<member><name>journal</name>
<value><string>Biofizika</string></value>
</member>
<member><name>volume</name>
<value><string>20</string></value>
</member>
<member><name>number</name>
<value><string>5</string></value>
</member>
<member><name>issn</name>
<value><string>0006-3029</string></value>
</member>
<member><name>pages</name>
<value><string>938-40</string></value>
</member>
<member><name>authors</name>
<value><array>
<data>
<value><string>Rikhireva G T</string></value>
<value><string>Pulatova M K</string></value>
<value><string>Chekulaeva L N</string></value>
<value><string>Druzhko A B</string></value>
<value><string>Kositsyna V A</string></value>
</data>
</array></value>
</member>
<member><name>year</name>
<value><string>1976</string></value>
</member>
<member><name>month</name>
<value><string>03</string></value>
</member>
<member><name>day</name>
<value><string>18</string></value>
</member>
</struct></value>
</param>
</params>
</methodResponse>